1135
00:58:19.278 --> 00:58:21.572
had led to a blind spot
in our work.


1136
00:58:21.655 --> 00:58:24.283
So, you know, we're kind
of trying to remedy that.


1137
00:58:24.366 --> 00:58:25.409
<i>And to that end,
I was wondering</i>


1138
00:58:25.492 --> 00:58:26.869
<i>how you might feel</i>

1139
00:58:27.119 --> 00:58:28.746
<i>about being a judge
in this year's award ceremony?</i>


1140
00:58:29.997 --> 00:58:32.833
Um, let me say first,

1141
00:58:32.916 --> 00:58:35.127
<i>Carl, that I'm honored
you choose me</i>


1142
00:58:35.210 --> 00:58:37.880
out of all the Black writers
you could go to out of fear


1143
00:58:37.963 --> 00:58:39.089
of being called racist.

1144
00:58:39.173 --> 00:58:41.300
Yeah, you're very welcome.

1145
00:58:41.383 --> 00:58:45.012
But I think this sounds
like a lot of work.


1146
00:58:45.095 --> 00:58:46.555
Yeah, I can't deny that.

1147
00:58:46.638 --> 00:58:48.557
I mean, you're going to have
to read dozens of books.


1148
00:58:48.640 --> 00:58:50.642
We could offer you
a modest stipend.


1149
00:58:51.560 --> 00:58:52.561
Even so, I'm not sure.

1150
00:58:53.187 --> 00:58:54.355
<i>Okay.</i>

1151
00:58:54.438 --> 00:58:55.856
One of the crass perk
I reference


1152
00:58:55.939 --> 00:58:57.566
when people are kind of
on the fence like this


1153
00:58:57.649 --> 00:58:59.443
is that this will allow you
the opportunity


1154
00:58:59.526 --> 00:59:01.695
to literally judge
these other writers for once,


1155
00:59:01.779 --> 00:59:02.946
rather than just figuratively.

1156
00:59:04.573 --> 00:59:05.866
All right, I'm in.

1157
00:59:05.949 --> 00:59:07.284
<i>Well, fantastic. Okay.</i>

1158
00:59:07.493 --> 00:59:10.037
Great. So you're going
to be one of five judges.


